## Critical — Constraints (No Exceptions)

- No redesign: colours, spacing, animations, brand tokens unchanged
- Minimal diffs: change only what is needed, never refactor for its own sake
- No fake data: schema, reviews, prices, phone numbers must be real or marked `[PLACEHOLDER]`
- No duplicated SEO blocks: one canonical, one H1, one schema block per page
- No new npm packages without PM approval and bundle size justification
- UK English throughout: colour, recognised, £ symbol
- All phone numbers as `<a href="tel:+44...">` — never plain text
- Every page must pass the SEO Pre-Completion Checklist before marking done

## Execution Phases

### Phase 0 — PM Pre-Flight (Before Any Code)

**Goal:** Audit current state, surface gaps, produce sprint plan.

1. **Codebase audit** — read key files: `app/layout.tsx`, `app/(public)/page.tsx`, `app/api/booking/route.ts`, `lib/db.ts`, `content/services.ts`, `content/areas.ts`, `content/reviews.ts`, `app/sitemap.ts`, `app/robots.ts`, `components/forms/BookingForm.tsx`, `components/layout/Header.tsx`, `components/layout/Footer.tsx`
2. **Gap analysis** — produce list for: DB gaps, API gaps, UI gaps, Content gaps, SEO gaps
3. **Sprint plan** — goal summary, agent execution order, files per phase, risks

### Phase 1 — Database (Full Setup)

**Agent:** Backend | **Dependency:** Phase 0

See `references/phase-details.md` for complete schema, migration runner, seed data, and DB utility layer specifications.

### Phase 2 — Backend & API Layer

**Agent:** Backend | **Dependency:** Phase 1

- Enhanced booking API with Zod validation + DB write + email send + rate limiting
- Contact/lead API endpoint
- Analytics event API endpoint
- Email templates via Resend
- Rate limiting on all public POST endpoints

### Phase 3 — Advanced UI

**Agent:** Frontend | **Dependency:** Phase 2

- Multi-step booking form (3 steps: service → details → confirmation)
- Sticky mobile CTA bar (Call Now + WhatsApp)
- Floating emergency badge (homepage + emergency page)
- Service cards enhancement (hover lift, icons, lazy images)
- Testimonials carousel (auto-advance, dots nav, accessible)
- Trust badges row (Gas Safe, 30+ Years, 4.6★, No Call-Out Fee)
- Breadcrumb component verification
- Cookie consent banner (UK law compliant)
- Loading/skeleton states

### Phase 4 — Advanced Content

**Agent:** Content + SEO | **Dependency:** Phase 3

- Homepage: 1,200–1,500 words, all 8 sections
- 10 service pages: 1,500–2,000 words each, all 10 sections
- 9 area pages: 800–1,200 words each, all 9 sections, >40% unique
- 6 blog posts: 1,200–1,500 words each, all 7 sections
- About page: 800–1,200 words, all 6 sections
- Reviews page: all 5 sections, data from DB

### Phase 5 — SEO Optimisation

**Agent:** SEO + Content | **Dependency:** Phase 4

- Root layout metadata fix (template pattern, no duplicate titles)
- Meta tags on every page (title, description, canonical, OG, Twitter, robots)
- Schema markup on every page (correct JSON-LD per page type)
- Internal linking audit (3-click max, no orphans)
- Sitemap + robots.txt verification
- OG images for all pages
- Phone number audit (zero placeholders)
- Core Web Vitals fixes

### Phase 6 — Analytics & Security

**Agent:** Analytics + Security | **Dependency:** Phase 5

- GA4 setup (cookie consent gated)
- Conversion event tracking (calls, WhatsApp, bookings, contacts)
- Security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- Input sanitisation audit
- Environment variable audit

### Phase 7 — QA Gate (Mandatory)

**Agent:** QA | **Dependency:** Phases 1–6

Run full QA checklist against every changed file: build, SEO, content, performance, accessibility, mobile, forms, security. Sprint is NOT complete until QA passes.

### Phase 8 — PM Report to Owner

Plain English report: what changed, what didn't change, QA result, placeholder items needing real data, next sprint backlog (top 5).

## Error Recovery

- If any phase fails, fix issues before proceeding to next phase
- If QA finds FAILs, fix inline — never defer
- If scope creep detected, pause and consult owner
- If a regression is introduced, revert and re-implement incrementally

